    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-03T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="219"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/323: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-03T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 3, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 8—3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>271. Your 144, July 6, 4 p.m. I explained to <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName> today our reasons for desiring to adhere to our text of
                    the draft of note, I also sent <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Henderson</persName>
                    to explain the matter to <persName corresp="#p_RBD1">Rosenblum</persName>,
                    Economic Adviser to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName> did not appear to be upset but
                    ended our conversation by saying “Well we shall see what we can do.”</p>
                <p>I gathered the impression that for political reasons he would like to accept our
                    proposal but that he felt he would have to take up the matter again with
                        <persName>Rosengoltz</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
